if ! test -f .henry_intro; then
	cat << henry_intro
The first cell consists of nothing more than a shoddily-made rack, a toilet, and concrete walls.
The wall opposite the rack has a poster of a sliding glass door and a bottle of window cleaner.
Nothing about it seems ordinary, least of all the occupant. 

A gaunt, raggeed looking man with a patchwork, smock-esque piece of clothing faces away from you 
in the cell, picking at his own fingers in a deep squat. He seems almost child-like, but when he
hears you step towards the cell, he ages 20 years. He sluggishly brings himself to his feet, 
turns toward you begrudgingly, and, with a little delay, begins talking...
henry_intro

touch .henry_intro

else
		cat << henry_statement
You won't find much of use from me, I was out exploring in the woods when the smith lost his anvil. 

I was trying to find myself some nice mushrooms to get through the next couple days in style, 

when I was immediately snatched up by the sheriff on my way back in! Now, I know I have a bit of a reputation, 

but this hardly seems fair, no? Next time I do something like this, you'll know princess. [end of statement]

