I see things that they don't see. I hear things that they don't hear. I know things that they don't know. I'm not crazy. I'm just awake.

They think I'm crazy because I believe in magic. They think I'm crazy because I believe in fairies. 

They think I'm crazy because I believe in the power of the mind. But they're wrong. 

Magic is real. Fairies are real. The power of the mind is real. I'm not crazy. I'm just open-minded.

They think I'm crazy because I talk to myself. They think I'm crazy because I laugh at nothing. They think I'm crazy because I dance in the street. But they're wrong. I'm not crazy. I'm just happy.

I'm happy because I know the truth. I know that the world is a magical place. 

I know that there are fairies and unicorns and dragons. 

I know that the power of the mind is limitless. 

I'm not crazy. 

I'm just enlightened.

So if you see me walking down the street, talking to myself and laughing at nothing, don't be afraid. 

