I sleep upside down. I prefer the company of squirrels. I see the world in a different way than most people.

I know that people think I'm crazy. They say that I'm a freak. But I don't care. I'm not going to change who I am.

I'm happy being different. I'm happy sleeping upside down. I'm happy with the company of squirrels.

Squirrels are my friends. They understand me. They don't judge me. They just accept me for who I am.

I love to watch them climb trees. I love to listen to them chatter. I love to feel their soft fur against my skin.

I know that some people think that I'm crazy. But I don't care. I'm happy with my life. I'm happy with my friends. I'm happy with who I am.

I'm hanging upside down from a tree branch. I'm watching a group of squirrels play. They're chasing each other, climbing trees, and burying nuts.

I smile. I love watching squirrels. They're so carefree and happy.

I close my eyes and listen to the sounds of the forest. I can hear the wind rustling through the leaves, the birds singing, and the squirrels chattering.

I feel at peace. I feel like I'm part of something bigger than myself.

I'm not crazy. I'm just different. And that's okay.

I know that some people will never understand me. But that's okay. I don't need them to understand me. I just need them to accept me for who I am.

